----------------------------------
RELEASE NOTES FOR VERSION 0.1.17
----------------------------------
USER VISIBLE CHANGES
Fixed: The number of maximum iteration (at population level) specified
by the user had not replaced the system's default value (=100).

OTHER CHANGES
The SPK-Compiler generated driver returns more information when
the program completes/terminates abnormally.  To be specific:
  0 = successful completion
  1 = optimization error
  2 = file/directory access error
  3 = post-integration error
  4 = statistics error
  5 = data simulation error
  >5 = unknown

